<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbb411a54-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1703"><num value="1703">§ 1703.</num><heading> “Contractor with the United States” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this subchapter, the term “contractor with the United States” includes any subcontractor or subordinate subcontractor with respect to the contract of such contractor.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbb411a55-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1942-12-02/ch668">Dec. 2, 1942, ch. 668</ref>, title I, § 103, <ref href="/us/stat/56/1031">56 Stat. 1031</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
